** Please be patient while the chart is being deployed **

Tip:

  Watch the deployment status using the command: kubectl get pods -w --namespace dev9

Services:

  echo Primary: test-db-mysql.dev9.svc.cluster.local:3306

Execute the following to get the administrator credentials:

  echo Username: root
  MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=$(kubectl get secret --namespace dev9 test-db-mysql -o jsonpath="{.data.mysql-root-password}" | base64 -d)

To connect to your database:

  1. Run a pod that you can use as a client:

      kubectl run test-db-mysql-client --rm --tty -i --restart='Never' --image  docker.io/bitnami/mysql:8.4.2-debian-12-r4 --namespace dev9 --env MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=$MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD --command -- bash

  2. To connect to primary service (read/write):

      mysql -h test-db-mysql.dev9.svc.cluster.local -uroot -p"$MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD"






